snippet.textDisplay:
0:00 Why are we only getting 12GB of VRAM? What is this early 2015? We're paying $200 more than the Titan X, to get the same 12GB capacity of VRAM, sure GDDR6 is reletively new being less than a year old for the 3080TI, where as GDDR5 was somthing like 6 or 7 years old for the Titan X, but come on. This card is 6 years older than the 3080TI, and you're going to charge us MORE for the same ammount of RAM? Not to mention we're not getting the full 100 class die, and not getting the Titan/Quadro drivers


The disturbing part is that if you want the equivalent 100 class ampere die to the MAxwell die that was in the Titan X ($999), you're going to have to shell out $10,400 for an Nvidia Ampere A100, and even that is a cut down card because it doesnt have video out like the Titan did.
